<!--
  Notification status-bar (small) icon.

  Android draws the small icon as an alpha-only silhouette, so the full-colour
  launcher icon renders as a solid white/black square. This is a dedicated
  white-on-transparent monochrome glyph (a wallet) so it renders correctly on
  every device. A vector is safe because the app's minSdk is 24 — the
  "bad notification" RemoteServiceException for vector small icons only affects
  API < 24.
-->
